---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Icon from '../components/Icon.astro';
import { contact } from '../data/contact.ts';

/*
  TERMS OF USE — first-pass draft, clearly marked DRAFT for counsel review.
  noindex stays until the owner approves. Canadian-law orientation; bracketed
  items are the few facts only the owner/counsel can supply (entity name,
  province).
*/
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of use" description="Terms of use for the ProofWipe website." noindex>
  <section class="container-page max-w-3xl py-16 lg:py-20">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-accent">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Terms of use</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">Effective date: [to be set at publication]</p>

    <div class="mt-6 flex items-start gap-3 rounded-lg border border-warning/40 bg-warning/10 p-4 text-sm">
      <Icon name="alert-triangle" size={18} class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-warning" />
      <p class="text-muted">
        <strong class="text-warning">DRAFT — for counsel review.</strong> This is
        first-pass wording pending legal review and owner approval. Excluded
        from search indexing until finalized.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-muted">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">1. Scope and acceptance</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          These terms govern your use of the ProofWipe website (proofwipe.com
          and proofwipe.ca), operated by [legal entity name] (“we”, “us”). By
          using the site you accept these terms. Use of the ProofWipe software
          is governed separately by the end-user licence agreement that
          accompanies the software; where the two conflict regarding the
          software, the licence agreement prevails.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">2. Downloads and integrity</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          ProofWipe is distributed exclusively through the official GitHub
          Releases page linked from this site. Verify the published SHA-256
          checksum before running any download. Copies obtained from any other
          source are not distributed by us, may have been altered, and are used
          entirely at your own risk.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">3. Responsible use of the software</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          ProofWipe permanently destroys data by design. You are solely
          responsible for: (a) ensuring you own, or are authorized by the owner
          to sanitize, any device you target; (b) selecting a sanitization
          category appropriate to your data sensitivity, policies, and legal
          obligations; and (c) verifying you have retained any data you need
          before sanitizing. Sanitized data cannot be recovered — that is the
          product's purpose.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">4. Standards and certification</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          ProofWipe implements published sanitization standards. It is not a
          third-party-certified product. Statements on this site describing
          standards alignment are informational and do not constitute
          certification, accreditation, or a guarantee of regulatory compliance
          for your organization; responsibility for your compliance program
          remains yours.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">5. No warranty</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The website and its content are provided “as is” and “as available”
          without warranties or conditions of any kind, whether express,
          implied, or statutory, including fitness for a particular purpose,
          merchantability, and non-infringement, to the maximum extent
          permitted by applicable law. Warranties applicable to the software
          itself, if any, are stated exclusively in its licence agreement.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">6. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, we are not liable
          for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or exemplary
          damages arising from use of this website — including loss of data,
          loss of profits, or business interruption — even if advised of the
          possibility. Nothing in these terms excludes liability that cannot be
          excluded under applicable law. [Counsel: consider an aggregate
          liability cap and whether Québec consumer-protection carve-outs are
          needed.]
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">7. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The ProofWipe name, logo, and all site content are the property of
          [legal entity name] or its licensors. You may not use the ProofWipe
          name or logo without prior written permission, except for factual
          reference to the product.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">8. Third-party links and services</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The site links to third-party services (GitHub for downloads,
          cyber.gc.ca for standards documents) and uses Formspree for contact
          delivery. Those services are governed by their own terms and privacy
          policies, which we do not control.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">9. Governing law</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          These terms are governed by the laws of [province] and the federal
          laws of Canada applicable therein. Courts located in [province] have
          exclusive jurisdiction over disputes arising from these terms or the
          website.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">10. Changes</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may update these terms from time to time; material changes will be
          posted on this page with an updated effective date. Continued use of
          the site after changes take effect constitutes acceptance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">11. Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Questions about these terms:
          <a href={`mailto:${contact.email}`} class="text-accent underline-offset-2 hover:underline">{contact.email}</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
